---
title: Sticky Miso Pork with Sweet Bell Peppers and Ginger Rice
description: Miso is a traditional Japanese condiment made by fermenting soybeans. You may recognize it from the very popular 'miso soup' but tonight, we're using miso in a whole new way. Pork is marinated in a combination of salty miso, tart rice vinegar and sweet soy-mirin blend. This sticky pork recipe is certainly something special!
